Outstanding food. We came here on recommendation from a friend who suggested the burger. We ordered the sourdough bread, onion salad, Diplomac burger, and the trout. All of these dishes were fantastic. The sourdough bread was amazing with the compound butter - definitely try it. You must get the Diplomac. This burger may actually be the best burger I have had. It‚Äôs nothing crazy, just a classic burger but done so ridiculously well. The American cheese in every bite was just something else. If you like burgers, you need to try this burger.

Cocktails were great and the beers and wines were also good. Service was great - the bartender took care of the bar whole room, not just the bar. Massively impressive because he was super polite and welcoming alongside that. Ambiance was also just cozy and great for a laid back date night.

TLDR: Definitely recommend and get the burger. I cannot wait to come back!

He offered to either leave us the dishes that he had taken back to the kitchen or that they could remake them. The remade pasta was a little better but it still had a harder chew texture than what you would expect, I wouldn‚Äôt be surprised if the same pasta was just reheated, just not a good enjoyable dish. In hindsight offering to try a non pasta dish as an alternative would‚Äôve been a better option if that‚Äôs how they serve all their pasta dishes.
